data.title: Spotless Brands appoints Matthew Schroeder as CFO & Jason O’Sullivan as SVP of IT to aid expansion into new markets.
data.description: A company based in Oakbrook Terrace, Illinois, Spotless Brands, has recently announced the addition of two new members to their Executive Leadership team to aid in their expansion into new markets. Matthew Schroeder has joined as the Chief Financial Officer (CFO) and Jason O'Sullivan as the Senior Vice President (SVP) of Information Technology (IT). This strategic move aims to strengthen the team as they navigate growth, with the goal of reaching new markets.

data.title: Vixxo hosts AI Hackathon in Scottsdale to innovate facilities management. 3-day event in 2025 brought together employees and students.
data.description: In Scottsdale, Arizona, Vixxo Facility Solutions recently organized an AI Innovation Hackathon at its headquarters, taking place from October 21 to 23, 2025. The event lasted for three days and saw participation from a range of employees spanning departments such as Operations, Supply Chain, Marketing, Client Success, IT Development, and Solutioning. In addition to employees, university students with outstanding skills also joined the event. Together, they worked on brainstorming and creating innovative solutions.

data.title: Sensient announces $0.41 per share dividend, payable on Dec 1, 2025, to shareholders on record by Nov 10, 2025.
data.description: The Board of Directors at Sensient Technologies Corporation (NYSE: SXT) has announced a regular quarterly cash dividend of $0.41 per share on its common stock. This dividend is scheduled to be paid on December 1, 2025, to shareholders holding stock as of the record date on November 10, 2025. Sensient Technologies Corporation is a prominent worldwide producer and distributor of colors, flavors, and specialty ingredients, utilizing innovative technologies and a strong global presence.

data.title: Wolverine Worldwide named 2025 Company of the Year by Footwear News, to be honored at FNAA in NYC on December 3.
data.description: Wolverine World Wide, Inc. (NYSE: WWW), a prominent company in the footwear and apparel industry, has been awarded the prestigious title of 2025 Company of the Year by Footwear News. This recognition will be celebrated at the Footwear News Achievement Awards (FNAA) on December 3 in New York City. The acknowledgment follows the Company's recent strategic transformation efforts, which have garnered success in a short span of two years. This achievement highlights Wolverine World Wide's position as a leader in the market.

data.title: Weis Markets declares $0.34 quarterly dividend to shareholders of record, payable November 24th. Founded in 1912.
data.description: Sunbury, Pennsylvania - On October 30, 2025, Weis Markets, Inc. (NYSE: WMK) announced that their Board of Directors approved a quarterly dividend of $0.34 per share. The dividend will be payable on November 24th to shareholders of record as of November 10th. Weis Markets, Inc. was established in 1912 and has been a prominent player in the industry since then.

data.title: Duplass Brothers Productions collaborates with Ink Films for 20th anniversary re-release of The Puffy Chair in 2026 nationwide.
data.description: In a recent announcement made on October 30, 2025, in Las Vegas, it was revealed that Ink Films is set to collaborate with Duplass Brothers Productions (DBP) for the 20th-anniversary re-release of the renowned independent film, The Puffy Chair, across the nation in 2026. This partnership marks an exciting development for the industry, sparking anticipation for the return of the Audience Award-winning film from the South by Southwest festival. Keep an eye out for this special cinematic event scheduled to take place in the coming year.

data.title: Coinbase (NASDAQ: COIN) stock rises after Q3 earnings release, beats estimates with $1.44 EPS and $1.86B revenue.
data.description: Shares of Coinbase Global Inc. (NASDAQ: COIN) surged following the release of their third-quarter earnings report, exceeding projections on both revenue and earnings. The company reported earnings of $1.44 per share, surpassing the analyst estimate of $1.11 by 29.38%. Quarterly revenue stood at $1.86 billion, outstripping the analyst consensus estimate. For real-time updates on COIN stock movement and to delve deeper into the full report, visit Benzinga.com.

data.title: Graco Inc. appoints Andrea H. Simon to its board of directors, effective Dec. 5, 2025. Ms. Simon currently serves as Executive VP & CFO at MasterBrand, Inc.
data.description: Graco Inc. (NYSE:GGG) has recently revealed the appointment of Andrea (Andi) H. Simon to their board of directors, with the effective date being December 5, 2025. Ms. Simon currently holds the position of Executive Vice President & Chief Financial Officer at MasterBrand, Inc. (NYSE: MBC), a prominent residential cabinet manufacturer in North America. She has been in this role since 2020 and continued her position even during the 2022 spin-off of MasterBrand as an independent public entity from Fortune.

data.title: Twilio's Q3 earnings beat expectations: Revenue at $1.3 billion, up 15% YoY, with over 392,000 active customer accounts.
data.description: Twilio Inc (NYSE: TWLO) released its Q3 financial report with some significant numbers. The company's revenue for the third quarter was $1.3 billion, surpassing the projected $1.25 billion as per Benzinga Pro. Adjusted earnings for the same period stood at $1.25 per share, exceeding the estimated $1.08 per share. There was a 15% year-over-year increase in total revenue. Twilio disclosed having over 392,000 active customer accounts by September 30. The complete article can be found on Benzinga.com, discussing Twilio's growing momentum.
